<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='471000' id='t-471000'>Every object in the opera comes alive and is a gigantic music instrument,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='475000' id='t-475000'>like this chandelier. It takes up the whole stage. It looks like a chandelier,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='478000' id='t-478000'>but it's actually a robotic music instrument.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='480000' id='t-480000'>So, as you can see in this prototype, gigantic piano strings,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='484000' id='t-484000'>each string is controlled with a little robotic element --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='487000' id='t-487000'>either little bows that stroke the strings, propellers that tickle the strings,</span>
